{"schema":"allo-reading-book@1","slug":"47971-where-is-my-mother","title":"Where is My Mother?","description":"A small baby bird is separated from its mother. The baby bird searches and searches for its mother but can’t find her. What will happen?","language":"English","langCode":"en","isRtl":false,"level":"2","orientation":"landscape","authors":["Alisha Berger"],"illustrators":["R. C. Pradeep Kumar"],"originalAuthors":[],"publisher":"Room to Read","license":"CC BY 4.0","licenseUrl":"https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/","sourceId":"storyweaver","contentType":"story","source":{"id":"storyweaver","name":"StoryWeaver, Pratham Books","url":"https://storyweaver.org.in/en/stories/47971-where-is-my-mother"},"cover":{"card":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/128583/size3/c7cc6b50e502c26ed6dc910456cb202c.jpg","large":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/128583/size6/c7cc6b50e502c26ed6dc910456cb202c.jpg"},"audio":null,"pages":[{"n":1,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/75163/size6/e8def1277a4c83cb0b30739157cb6217.jpg","text":"Baby bird wakes up.","words":null},{"n":2,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/75164/size6/d5c58d9ccb3dfa4266d2c33b0778f4e0.jpg","text":"Her mother is missing!","words":null},{"n":3,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/75165/size6/de32c7aab7f6c005da75ae8f3e6c47a0.jpg","text":"Baby tries to fly in search of her mother.","words":null},{"n":4,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/75166/size6/dbea9fbfdcde4fac8af662b604d29328.jpg","text":"Oh no!\nShe cannot fly yet.","words":null},{"n":5,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/75167/size6/ff28a19eadf87a2a900f86f54ecd5db5.jpg","text":"“Are you my mother?” Baby asks the crow.\n“Kaa! Kaa! Not me!” the crow says.","words":null},{"n":6,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/75168/size6/55f618f0aad64f2b52b1b48ca777b655.jpg","text":"“Are you my mother?” Baby asks the hen.\n “Cukuruk-koo! Not me!” the hen says.","words":null},{"n":7,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/75169/size6/7a60b7ae71f9a9e329a69a775ab9f5b5.jpg","text":"“Are you my mother?” Baby asks duck.\n “Quack! Quack! Not me!\" the duck says.","words":null},{"n":8,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/75170/size6/40e20db175887183f806ccf47f2af1fe.jpg","text":"Maybe if I call for my mother loudly, she will hear me, Baby thinks.\n“Cheep! Cheep! Cheep-cheep!”","words":null},{"n":9,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/75171/size6/02fa36831166d9265cb4f13c7e19ceae.jpg","text":"Mother hears Baby and comes flying.","words":null},{"n":10,"img":"https://storage.googleapis.com/static.storyweaver.org.in/illustration_crops/75172/size6/4ce5b99b7eb8be315cf97fc0fbb10dde.jpg","text":"They fly happily together into the sky.\nHooray!","words":null}],"stats":{"pages":10,"words":97}}